          <p id="SADC.IO.4">The first Southern African Development Co-ordination Conference (SADCC) was held in July 1979, to harmonize development plans and to reduce the region's eco­nomic dependence on South Africa. In August 1992 the 10 member countries of the SADCC signed a Treaty establishing the SADC, which replaced the SADCC upon its entry into force in October 1993. The Treaty places binding obligations on member countries, with the aim of promoting economic integration towards a fully developed common market. The Treaty was amended in 2001 to institutionalize closer social and political co-operation.</p>
