          <int-org-section id="SADC.IO.63" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Summit Meeting</heading>
               <p id="SADC.IO.20">Heads of state and of government or their representatives meet at least once a year. The meeting is the supreme policymaking organ of SADC and is responsible for the appointment of the Executive Secretary. It is managed by a troika system, comprising the current, incoming and previous chairpersons. The 43rd regular summit was hosted by Angola in August 2023, in its capital, Luanda. An extraordinary summit was convened, in a virtual format, in early February 2024 to consider the cholera situation in the region.</p>
